00:00:03.890 --> 00:00:07.725
Now that you've learned
about flexbox and grid,

00:00:07.725 --> 00:00:09.705
it's time to compare them

00:00:09.705 --> 00:00:12.180
side-by-side to see which one

00:00:12.180 --> 00:00:14.205
you should use for
which purpose.

00:00:14.205 --> 00:00:16.560
Well, let me mention
that sometimes there

00:00:16.560 --> 00:00:19.020
is no right or wrong way when it

00:00:19.020 --> 00:00:20.430
comes to web development

00:00:20.430 --> 00:00:22.110
because you can achieve
something using

00:00:22.110 --> 00:00:26.145
grid and you may achieve the
same thing using a flexbox.

00:00:26.145 --> 00:00:28.740
So sometimes it all comes to

00:00:28.740 --> 00:00:33.045
our preferences and how we
want to structure our website.

00:00:33.045 --> 00:00:35.205
Therefore, I'm going to
show you some examples

00:00:35.205 --> 00:00:37.560
to understand the
difference better.

00:00:37.560 --> 00:00:39.770
First of all, you need
to know that when

00:00:39.770 --> 00:00:42.185
we have one-dimensional layouts,

00:00:42.185 --> 00:00:44.990
it's probably best
to use a Flexbox,

00:00:44.990 --> 00:00:47.450
but sometimes if you
want to make our design

00:00:47.450 --> 00:00:50.465
responsive and make
our life much easier,

00:00:50.465 --> 00:00:53.645
we can do the same
thing using a grid.

