So here I have a card
inside this section.

00:00:56.450 --> 00:00:59.255
I'm gonna go ahead and
add a container here.

00:00:59.255 --> 00:01:01.475
I'm going to drag and
drop a container.

00:01:01.475 --> 00:01:05.000
And then let me add the
class container to that.

00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:07.190
And finally, I'm
going to drag and

00:01:07.190 --> 00:01:09.439
drop this card
into my container.

00:01:09.439 --> 00:01:14.420
Nice. Now I'm going to copy
it and paste it three times.

00:01:14.420 --> 00:01:15.020
Okay?

00:01:15.020 --> 00:01:17.270
Alright, let me
select my section

00:01:17.270 --> 00:01:19.880
since I turned it
to a flexbox and

00:01:19.880 --> 00:01:22.640
now I'm going to select
my container and I'm

00:01:22.640 --> 00:01:25.460
going to change the display
setting to flex max.

00:01:25.460 --> 00:01:28.415
And here we have a
horizontal Flexbox.

00:01:28.415 --> 00:01:30.980
And as you can see,
everything looks great.

00:01:30.980 --> 00:01:34.070
I can change the
justification to

00:01:34.070 --> 00:01:37.865
space between two
space around left,

00:01:37.865 --> 00:01:40.010
middle, whatever I want.

00:01:40.010 --> 00:01:43.385
But now I'm using a
one-dimensional layout.

00:01:43.385 --> 00:01:46.250
If I have two
containers like this,

00:01:46.250 --> 00:01:49.175
now we have a
two-dimensional layout.

00:01:49.175 --> 00:01:52.790
It probably makes more
sense to use a grid.

00:01:52.790 --> 00:01:56.030
Now let's check this layout
on different breakpoints.

00:01:56.030 --> 00:01:58.340
I'm gonna go to tablets
and as you can see,

00:01:58.340 --> 00:02:01.160
it shrinks. Okay, nice.

00:02:01.160 --> 00:02:05.210
However, if you want to make
our design more responsive,

00:02:05.210 --> 00:02:08.405
it would make sense to
use a grid as well,

00:02:08.405 --> 00:02:11.000
even for one-dimensional layout,

00:02:11.000 --> 00:02:12.755
It's totally up to you.

00:02:12.755 --> 00:02:14.315
As I mentioned before,

00:02:14.315 --> 00:02:16.790
there is no right or wrong way.

00:02:16.790 --> 00:02:19.490
Sometimes we just
need to focus on

00:02:19.490 --> 00:02:21.800
our preferences and
focus on the fact

00:02:21.800 --> 00:02:24.470
that which way suits
our needs better.

